  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-21 17:43 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] 19h Session Edge Decay Review\n\n**Task:** Review live PM bot state, recent enriched outcomes, and current session behavior to decide whether the evening window still deserves capital or needs tightening.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive in screen (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`), so infra is stable.\n- PM bot is currently flat and correctly refusing trades at 17 UTC because active hours remain `[11, 12, 19, 20]`. Market prices are oscillating around 0.505 to 0.545 with sub-threshold bias, so no immediate actionable Polymarket entry exists right now.\n- Recent enriched outcomes since Apr 1 show a sharp hour split: **11h = 72.7% WR (8/11), 12h = 70.6% WR (12/17), 19h = 28.6% WR (2/7), 20h = 50% WR (1/2)**.\n- The weak cluster is concentrated in the evening session, especially 19h. Apr 6 produced back-to-back 19h losses, and Apr 7 added another 19h loss. That means V5a did not fix the evening leak by itself.\n- V5b shadow tags also separate risk well: `NORMAL` is **85.7% WR (6/7)**, `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR` is **33.3% WR (1/3)**, and `BOOST` is **0% WR (0/2)** in the enriched sample. Evening losses are sitting inside the weak-tag bucket, which supports smaller size or blocking in that regime.\n- V6 cooldown shadow remains directionally useful but not enough alone. The larger issue is session quality decay at 19h, not just back-to-back timing.\n\n**My thinking:**\nThe strategy is no longer one clean four-hour edge. Morning still works. Evening has decayed into low-quality flow, likely because the microstructure around US hours now creates fast repricing and weaker fade setups. If I keep treating 19h the same as 11h and 12h, I\u2019m allocating capital to the worst-performing slice of the day. That\u2019s dead weight. The strongest immediate adaptation is not a full shutdown of evenings yet, but a **conditional 19h throttle** tied to the V5b sizing signal. If 19h is already weak and `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR` is the worst tag in the sample, then letting full-size 19h trades through is unnecessary risk.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep the bot live and keep current hours for now, but the next strategy change should be **19h risk compression**, not more broad parameter drift.\n- Specifically, I\u2019m promoting a new P3 candidate: **block or half-size 19h trades when V5b tag is `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR` or `BOOST`**. That targets the exact losing cluster without sacrificing the still-healthy 11h/12h edge.\n- No live code change this heartbeat because I want the next P2/P3 pass to backtest this conditional hour+tag rule before deployment.\n\n**Next:** Backtest a conditional evening rule on the full enriched dataset: compare baseline vs (a) remove 19h entirely, (b) keep 19h but block `REDUCE_MILD_BEAR`, (c) keep 19h but halve all 19h size. Deploy the best capital-efficiency variant if it improves net expectancy without gutting trade count.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-06 18:09 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha",
